Sample_growth_protocol_ch1: U2OS cells and HEK293 cells were grown in DMEM supplemented with 10% fetal bovine serum and 1% penicillin/streptomycin until 80% confluent. HepG2 cells  were grown in EMEM with 10% FBS and 1% penicillin and streptomycin. K562 cells were grown in RPMI supplemented with 10% heat-inactivated FBS, 2 mM GlutaMax, and 1% penicillin and streptomycin.
Sample_extract_protocol_ch1: For RNA-seq, total RNA was extracted from native cells using the NucleoSpin RNA Plus Kit (Clontech, cat# 740984.250), Single-end libraries were prepared using the Illumina TruSeq Stranded Total RNA Library Prep Gold kit (Illumina) and TruSeq RNA Single Indexes, pooled, and sequenced using an NextSeq500.
Sample_data_processing: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: Tab-delimited text files that include FPKM values for each gene
RNA-seq reads were aligned to hg19 using: 10.1093/bioinformatics/bts635) and PCR duplicates were removed using Picard tools(http://broadinstitute.github.io/picard/). Reads aligning to ribosomal RNA were then filtered out of the alignment. Genomic coverage from filtered alignments were calculated by normalizing to sequencing depth using bedtools(https://doi.org/10.1093/bioinformatics/btq033). FPKMs were calculated using Cufflinks(https://doi.org/10.1038/nbt.1621)

Sample_growth_protocol_ch1: U2OS cells and HEK293 cells were grown in DMEM supplemented with 10% fetal bovine serum and 1% penicillin/streptomycin until 80% confluent. HepG2 cells  were grown in EMEM with 10% FBS and 1% penicillin and streptomycin. K562 cells were grown in RPMI supplemented with 10% heat-inactivated FBS, 2 mM GlutaMax, and 1% penicillin and streptomycin.
Sample_extract_protocol_ch1: For ChIP-seq, chromatin from 1% formaldehyde-fixed cells were fragmented to 200-500 bps by sonication for 5-6 mins using the Branson sonifer SFX250, Sequencing libraries were prepared with 3 ng of each H3K27Ac ChIP DNA and input sample using SMARTer ThruPLEX DNA-seq kit (Takara, Cat# R400675). Libraries were sequenced with single-end (SE) 75 cycles on an Illumina Nextseq 500 system
Sample_data_processing: ChIP-seq reads were aligned to human reference genome hg19 using Burrows-Wheeler Alignment (BWA) tool (PMC2705234). Genome-wide coverage was calculated after extending to 200 bases(approximate fragment size) and averaged over 25 bp windows using igvtools (https://doi.org/10.1093/bib/bbs017). Coverage was then normalized and scaled using RSeqC (http://rseqc.sourceforge.net/#normalize-bigwig-py)
Supplementary_files_format_and_content: bigwig files for visualization on igv

Sample_growth_protocol_ch1: U2OS cells and HEK293 cells were grown in DMEM supplemented with 10% fetal bovine serum and 1% penicillin/streptomycin until 80% confluent. HepG2 cells  were grown in EMEM with 10% FBS and 1% penicillin and streptomycin. K562 cells were grown in RPMI supplemented with 10% heat-inactivated FBS, 2 mM GlutaMax, and 1% penicillin and streptomycin.
Sample_extract_protocol_ch1: For ATAC-seq, cells (5 x 104) were incubated with DNase I (Worthington cat# LS002007) to remove DNA from dead cells, washed with PBS, resuspended in lysis buffer, and treated with transposase from Nextera DNA sample Prep Kit (Illumina, cat# FC-121-1030)., Libraries were made through adding adpators on purified tagmented DNA, followed by double-sided bead purification. Purified products were sequenced with PE 150 cycles on an Illumina Nextseq500 system
Sample_data_processing: ATAC-seq Reads aligned to hg19 using BWA. Properly aligned reads were filtered to exclude PCR duplicates and processed as previously described (PMC3959825). Read start positions were shifted towards the 3’ end by 4 bp in for reads aligning to plus strand and 5 bp towards the 5’ end for reads aligning to minus strand.
Supplementary_files_format_and_content: bigwig files for visualization on igv
